description.narrative: Enhanced South-South Collaboration has strengthened capacities within the governments and boosted the effectiveness of the programmes. Increased evidence on the needs of adolescent and youth at risk has also enabled EAPRO to conduct effective policy advocacy on emerging health and HIV issues and promote partnerships between governments and youth. Increased collaboration with other development partners provided a more coordinated approach to strengthen country capacity and mobilised resources for emerging needs, such as increased outbreaks. Increasing engagement with ASEAN could help to address different needs of countries and advance the health agenda. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/08/2020
